rough the global political economy in the transitional moment of American decline and Chinese ascension. With an explicit focus of state economic policy, IMF cinema did not just depict the economy; it also was this economy's material embodiment. That is, it both represented economic developments and was itself an important sector in which the same pressures and changes affecting the economy at large were at work. Joseph Jonghyun Jeon's window on Korea provides a peripheral but crucial perspective on the operations of late US hegemony and the contradictions that ultimately corrode it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aEconomics in motion pictures. 0aMotion picture industryzKorea (South)xHistory. 0aMotion pictureszKorea (South)xHistory. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAmerican studies.  aAsian Marxism.  aAsian studies.  aIMF Crisis.  aK-pop.  aKorea.  aUS hegemony.  acultures of economics.  afilm.  aglobalization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2020z9783110704655oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360846740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503608467423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503608467.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070478-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture 